h Astro, Markdown and ~140 lines of CSS.","The first project on this site is the site itself.\n\n**Goal:** a fast, minimal personal site where adding content means\nwriting a Markdown file — nothing more.\n\n**Stack:**\n\n- [Astro](https://astro.build) compiles Markdown into plain HTML pages\n- One hand-written CSS file, no framework\n- Hosted free on GitHub Pages, deployed automatically on `git push`\n\n**Source:** [github.com/yourusername/yourusername.github.io](https://github.com/yourusername)","src/content/projects/this-website.md","bc1198dad6e38516",{"html":21,"metadata":22},"\u003Cp>The first project on this site is the site itself.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Goal:\u003C/strong> a fast, minimal personal site where adding content means\nwriting a Markdown file — nothing more.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Stack:\u003C/strong>\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Ca href=\"https://astro.build\">Astro\u003C/a> compiles Markdown into plain HTML pages\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>One hand-written CSS file, no framework\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>Hosted free on GitHub Pages, deployed automatically on \u003Ccode>git push\u003C/code>\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Source:\u003C/strong> \u003Ca href=\"https://github.com/yourusername\">github.com/yourusername/yourusername.github.io\u003C/a>\u003C/p>",{"headings":23,"localImagePaths":24,"remoteImagePaths":25,"frontmatter":26,"imagePaths":28},[],[],[],{"title":14,"date":27,"description":16},["Date","2026-06-09T00:00:00.000Z"],[],"essays",["Map",31,32,49,50],"ai-and-politics",{"id":31,"data":33,"body":37,"filePath":38,"digest":39,"rendered":40},{"title":34,"date":35,"description":36},"How AI is reshaping Politics",["Date","2026-06-15T00:00:00.000Z"],"A personal essay about the impact of AI on political processes.","This is a placeholder essay — replace it with your first real one.\n\nWriting forces clarity. An idea that feels solid in my head often falls\napart the moment I try to put it into sentences, and that collapse is\nuseful: it shows me exactly what I don't understand yet.\n\nPublishing adds a second pressure. Knowing that someone might read this\nmakes me check my claims, define my terms, and finish my thoughts. Even\nif nobody reads it, the discipline remains.\n\n> If you can't explain it simply, you don't understand it well enough.\n\nSo this site is less a showcase than a workbench, in public.","src/content/essays/ai-and-politics.md","5f2fb0a20fb8b5a6",{"html":41,"metadata":42},"\u003Cp>This is a placeholder essay — replace it with your first real one.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Writing forces clarity. An idea that feels solid in my head often falls\napart the moment I try to put it into sentences, and that collapse is\nuseful: it shows me exactly what I don’t understand yet.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>Publishing adds a second pressure. Knowing that someone might read this\nmakes me check my claims, define my terms, and finish my thoughts. Even\nif nobody reads it, the discipline remains.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cblockquote>\n\u003Cp>If you can’t explain it simply, you don’t understand it well enough.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/blockquote>\n\u003Cp>So this site is less a showcase than a workbench, in public.\u003C/p>",{"headings":43,"localImagePaths":44,"remoteImagePaths":45,"frontmatter":46,"imagePaths":48},[],[],[],{"title":34,"date":47,"description":36},["Date","2026-06-15T00:00:00.000Z"],[],"writing-in-public",{"id":49,"data":51,"body":37,"filePath":55,"digest":56,"rendered":57},{"title":52,"date":53,"description":54},"Why I'm Writing in Public",["Date","2026-06-10T00:00:00.000Z"],"The reasoning behind this site.","src/content/essays/writing-in-public.md","3816c6cd64d57608",{"html":41,"metadata":58},{"headings":59,"localImagePaths":60,"remoteImagePaths":61,"frontmatter":62,"imagePaths":64},[],[],[],{"title":52,"date":63,"description":54},["Date","2026-06-10T00:00:00.000Z"],[],"blog",["Map",67,68],"binary-search",{"id":67,"data":69,"body":73,"filePath":74,"digest":75,"rendered":76},{"title":70,"date":71,"description":72},"Binary Search, and Why It's O(log n)",["Date","2026-06-11T00:00:00.000Z"],"My notes on binary search: the algorithm, an implementation, and where the logarithm comes from.","This post exists to show you everything a blog post here can contain:\nplain text, code with syntax highlighting, and math. Delete it once you\nhave written your own first post.\n\n## The idea\n\nBinary search finds a value in a **sorted** array by repeatedly cutting\nthe search range in half. Compare the middle element to the target: if\nit's too small, the answer must be in the right half; too big, the left\nhalf.\n\n## An implementation\n\n```python\ndef binary_search(arr, target):\n    lo, hi = 0, len(arr) - 1\n    while lo \u003C= hi:\n        mid = (lo + hi) // 2\n        if arr[mid] == target:\n            return mid\n        elif arr[mid] \u003C target:\n            lo = mid + 1\n        else:\n            hi = mid - 1\n    return -1\n```\n\n## Where the logarithm comes from\n\nEach step halves the range, so after $k$ steps the range has size\n$n / 2^k$. The search ends when the range reaches size 1:\n\n$$\n\\frac{n}{2^k} = 1 \\iff k = \\log_2 n\n$$\n\nSo the number of steps grows logarithmically: the complexity is\n$O(\\log n)$. Doubling the array adds just *one* extra step.","src/content/blog/binary-search.md","42ce637c9366bb23",{"html":77,"metadata":78},"\u003Cp>This post exists to show you everything a blog post here can contain:\nplain text, code with syntax highlighting, and math. Delete it once you\nhave written your own first post.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"the-idea\">The idea\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Binary search finds a value in a \u003Cstrong>sorted\u003C/strong> array by repeatedly cutting\nthe search range in half. Compare the middle element to the target: if\nit’s too small, the answer must be in the right half; too big, the left\nhalf.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"an-implementation\">An implementation\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cpre class=\"astro-code astro-code-themes github-light github-dark\" style=\"--shiki-light:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#e1e4e8;--shiki-light-bg:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#24292e; overflow-x: auto;\" tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"python\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">def\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#B392F0\"> binary_search\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">(arr, target):\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">    lo, hi \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF\"> 0\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">, \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF\">len\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">(arr) \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">-\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF\"> 1\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">    while\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> lo \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">&#x3C;=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> hi:\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">        mid \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> (lo \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">+\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> hi) \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">//\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF\"> 2\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">        if\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> arr[mid] \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">==\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> target:\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">            return\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> mid\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">        elif\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> arr[mid] \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">&#x3C;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> target:\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">            lo \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\"> mid \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">+\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#79B8FF\"> 1\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">        else\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">:\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E4E8\">            hi \u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F97583\">=\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#E1E